## Summary Table of Apartheid’s Effects on Different Life Aspects

| Aspect                 | Impact on Non-White South Africans                                  | Long-Term Consequences                          |
|------------------------|--------------------------------------------------------------------|------------------------------------------------|
| **Political Rights**    | Denied voting rights and political representation                  | Continued political activism and social unrest |
| **Movement & Residence**| Restricted movement; forced removals; pass laws                    | Segregated urban geography; social fragmentation|
| **Employment**          | Labor market discrimination; low wages; no union rights           | Entrenched poverty and economic inequality     |
| **Education**           | Inferior, segregated education systems                             | Educational disparities and skill gaps         |
| **Healthcare**          | Segregated and under-resourced healthcare                          | Poor health outcomes and higher mortality      |
| **Psychological**       | Trauma from systemic racism and violence                           | Generational mental health challenges           |
| **Cultural Identity**  | Forced racial classification and cultural suppression              | Loss of cultural heritage and identity issues  |

